# Input, Output, and Arguments

## User Input
read username
echo "Hello $username"

## Script Arguments
$0 → script name
$1 → first argument
$2 → second argument
$@ → all arguments
$# → number of arguments

Example:
./deploy.sh prod us-east-1

## Output Redirection
>  overwrite
>> append

ls > files.txt
date >> files.txt

## Error Redirection
command 2> error.log
command &> all.log

## DevOps Use Case
Used in pipelines to capture logs and pass environment-specific values.
